More and more forces mobilized for giant strike
The League of Trade Unions and the Hungarian Trade Union Federation will form their coordination committee on Friday for the indefinite strike beginning on Monday.
A large protest assembly will be held on Saturday, on Monday - the day of the referendum on the health insurance law - the dismissal of work begins.
It is expected that there will be significant strike-related traffic disabilities, as railway traffic is almost completely discontinued, and the Budapest public transport companies (BKV) will also strike until 1 p.m.
Details of Monday’s strike will be announced jointly by the union league and the union federation on Friday afternoon.
A LIGA-MOSZ strike committee will also be established, responsible for coordinating the actions on Monday.
A large protest assembly will be held on Saturday, and from Monday all organizations joining the strike will set up work for an indefinite period of time, unless agreement is reached with the government.
In other words, the end of the strike starting on the day of the parliamentary vote on the health insurance law was not defined.
If the National Council does not adopt the Health Insurance Act, the unions immediately withdraw the call for strike.
However, if the law is passed, the strike shoots meet to discuss further action.
