Astronauts, who originally left the Discovery spacecraft for a control process and then repaired another solar panel whose rotation system was faulty, were forced to devote themselves to the damaged collector.
And Scott Parazynski was chosen to walk around at the end of the 30 meter long remotely controlled arm of the spacecraft on which the station had been attached to perform the repair.
