The tool he used, a mini hockey club, wrapped with an insulator to prevent an electrical blow on the solar panels that produce several hundred volts, the astronauts on board the station had invented and crafted.
When the action was over, Scott Parazynski waited until the collector was fully unfolded before he counted his tools and returned to the station.
