Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance covering a possible damage caused by the driver involves a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of issuance of the driver’s license, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Having a car is only the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we have to be clear about what we have to do here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is entered into in writing by means of an insurance contract which establishes that the company receives the insurance premium agreed and in return is obliged to provide the corresponding compensation amount in the event of a damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance composed of several factors, including age, gender, date of creation of the driver’s license, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices in accordance with statistics, so that if a higher risk of accidents occurs, higher contributions will also be paid.
For this reason, both women and women over the age of 25 need to make less contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married individuals, since they, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of companies, tend to have fewer accidents as single individuals.
The benefit given to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
At this point, we list the most important points to consider when choosing insurance in order to be able to make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under the age of 25 are facing numerous obstacles when choosing an affordable insurance, such as low driving practice and young driving license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance coverage to take a full-case insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Cautious drivers can choose a full cash with self-employment, so that the services of a full cash insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay a portion of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined prior to the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the sum to be paid , explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s chief representative at First Europa, a brokerage company for online insurance.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against damage to the own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to lower your insurance costs, so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the base rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said rate.
The amount of credits and penalties will depend on the company and its income.
If the company has a high-profit year behind it, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract, because with increasing driving practice, the accident rate is decreasing.
Thus, it is most useful to opt for a full-case insurance with self-employment.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish executive of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner was removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married client who does not have children to take full cash insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the person concerned allows.
Insurers consider married couples with children to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and consequently their contributions are low.
In this case, a full cash insurance with self-employment (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which uses only for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to set up a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For retirees, it is advisable to enter into a full-case insurance with self-employment (at an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance that only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, you have to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection to be made in accordance with our personal situation.
